    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban leaseholders from having no pets clauses",
        "additional_details": "I am presently purchasing a ground floor flat in what was previously a local authority block. It is now under the management of a housing association who are the leaseholders of the block. My visitors will be allowed to bring their dogs with them, despite my dog being prohibited from living with me.",
        "background": "The Government should recognise that leaseholders are putting restrictions on purchasers and tenants to say that they can\u2019t own pets, such as a companion dog. Some people are choosing to remain homeless rather than be parted from their beloved companion.\r\n",
